  "text": "The Kafka Connect REST API is implemented through the following key components:\n\n## REST API Handler Resources\n\nThe main REST API endpoints are handled by **ConnectorsResource** (sg-evals/kafka--0753c489/connect/runtime/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/connect/runtime/rest/resources/ConnectorsResource.java), which is registered at the @Path(\"/connectors\") endpoint. This resource provides endpoints for managing connectors and their tasks:\n\n- **getConnectorStatus** (line 181-183): Handles GET /connectors/{connector}/status requests\n- **getTaskStatus** (line 321-325): Handles GET /connectors/{connector}/tasks/{task}/status requests\n- **listConnectors** (line 103-136): Lists all connectors with optional expansion for status and info\n- **createConnector** (line 138-158): Creates new connectors\n- **restartConnector** (line 250-276): Restarts connectors and/or tasks\n\nAdditional resources include:\n- **RootResource** (sg-evals/kafka--0753c489/connect/runtime/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/connect/runtime/rest/resources/RootResource.java): Handles root endpoint and health checks\n- **ConnectorPluginsResource** (sg-evals/kafka--0753c489/connect/runtime/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/connect/runtime/rest/resources/ConnectorPluginsResource.java): Provides plugin information and configuration validation\n\n## Task Status and Error Response Schemas\n\nThe REST API uses two main response schema classes:\n\n### ConnectorStateInfo (sg-evals/kafka--0753c489/connect/runtime/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/connect/runtime/rest/entities/ConnectorStateInfo.java)\n\nThis entity represents the complete state of a connector and its tasks. It contains:\n- **name**: String - connector name\n- **connector**: ConnectorState - state of the connector instance\n- **tasks**: List<TaskState> - state of all tasks for the connector\n- **type**: ConnectorType - whether it's a source or sink connector\n\nThe **AbstractState** inner class (lines 64-98) defines shared state fields:\n- **state**: String - current state (RUNNING, PAUSED, FAILED, UNASSIGNED, RESTARTING, STOPPED)\n- **workerId**: String (\"worker_id\" in JSON) - ID of the worker running this connector/task\n- **trace**: String - error trace message if failed (can be null/empty)\n- **version**: String - plugin/connector version information\n\nThe **TaskState** class (lines 111-147) extends AbstractState and adds:\n- **id**: int - the task ID within the connector\n\nThe **ConnectorState** class (lines 100-109) extends AbstractState for connector-level status.\n\n### ErrorMessage (sg-evals/kafka--0753c489/connect/runtime/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/connect/runtime/rest/entities/ErrorMessage.java)\n\nThis entity represents error responses from the REST API:\n- **errorCode**: int (\"error_code\" in JSON) - numeric error code\n- **message**: String - human-readable error message\n\nThese errors are generated automatically by the ConnectExceptionMapper when uncaught ConnectExceptions occur.\n\n## Backend Implementation\n\nThe status information is generated by:\n\n**AbstractHerder** (sg-evals/kafka--0753c489/connect/runtime/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/connect/runtime/AbstractHerder.java):\n- **connectorStatus** (line 350-365): Builds ConnectorStateInfo from status backing store\n- **taskStatus** (line 392-400): Retrieves task-specific status\n\n**KafkaStatusBackingStore** (sg-evals/kafka--0753c489/connect/runtime/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/connect/storage/KafkaStatusBackingStore.java):\n- Stores connector and task status in Kafka topic \"connect-status\"\n- Manages status persistence and retrieval\n\n## Version Information in Responses\n\nIn the current codebase (commit 0753c489), the REST API includes version information in the status response through the \"version\" field in both ConnectorStateInfo.AbstractState and its subclasses. This field contains the connector/task implementation version and is conditionally included in JSON responses via the @JsonInclude filter (line 94).\n\n**Note**: The codebase does not show distinct v1 and v2 REST API endpoint paths or separate handlers. Instead, versioning is handled through:\n1. A single unified REST API endpoint structure at /connectors\n2. Version information included as a field within responses\n3. Backward compatibility through the version field filtering mechanism\n\nThe core connector status response schema includes state, worker ID, error trace, and version fields, providing comprehensive status information for both v1 and v2 compatibility."
}

